Disorder of sex development

Sex chromosome DSD

  • Turner syndrome (45X)
  • Klinefelter syndrome (47XXY)
  • Mixed gonadal dysgenesis (45X / 46XY)
  • Chimerism

46XX DSD

  • Ovarian development
  • Gonadal dysgenesis
  • Ovotesticular DSD
  • Testicular DSD = เป็น XX เเต่มี SRY gene
  • Androgen excess
  • 21-hydroxylase deficiency
  • 11-hydroxylase deficiency
  • Placental aromatase deficiency
  • Maternal androgen exposure

46XY DSD

  • Testicular development
  • Gonadal dysgenesis
  • Ovotesticular DSD
  • Testis regression
  • Androgen deficiency
  • Smith-Lemli-Opitz syndrome = cholesterol synthetic defect
  • LH receptor defect = testosterone synthetic defect
  • 5α-reductase deficiency = testosterone ไม่เปลี่ยนเป็น DHT
  • Androgen insensitivity syndrome

21-hydroxylase deficiency

  • Female
  • Hyperpigmentation
  • Ambiguous genitalia
  • ↑ACTH & ↓cortisol
  • ↑testosterone
  • Male = เด็กผู้ชายกว่าจะรู้ก็จะมาด้วย dehydration
  • Hyperpigmentation
  • Normal genitalia
  • ↑ACTH & ↓cortisol
  • ↓aldosterone = ↓water & Na
  • ↑testosterone

Physiology of puberty

Disorder of puberty

Precocious puberty (early)

  • Female = breast development < 8y
  • Male = testicular enlargement < 9y

  • Cause
  • Gonadotropin-dependent (central) = ↑Est & ↑LH/FSH
  • Idiopathic
  • Hypothalamic hamartoma
  • Hypothalamic-pituitary tumor
  • Hydrocephalus
  • Genetic

  • Gonadotropin-independent (peripheral) = ↑Est & ↓LH/FSH (โดย Est ยับยั่ง)
  • McCune-Albright syndrome (GNAS mutation)
  • Ovarian cyst
  • LH receptor mutation
  • hCG-producing tumor
  • Adrenocortical tumor
  • Congenital adrenal hyperplasia
  • Exogenous steroid

Delayed puberty

  • Female = breast development > 13y
  • Male = testicular enlargement > 14y

  • Cause
  • Hypogonadotropic hypogonadism (central) = ↓Est & ↓LH/FSH
  • Congenital
  • Kallmann syndrome
  • Isolated gonadotropin deficiency
  • Multiple pituitary hormone deficiency
  • Acquired
  • Prolactinoma
  • Pituitary hemochromatosis
  • Hypergonadotropic hypogonadism (peripheral) = ↓Est & ↑LH/FSH
  • Congenital
  • Turner syndrome
  • Klinefelter syndrome
  • Gonadal dysgenesis
  • Acquired
  • Autoimmune
  • Mump (infection)

Kallmann syndrome

  • Cause = abnormal migration of GnRH neuron to hypothalamus
  • Clinical feature
  • delayed puberty
  • Hyposmia /anosmia (การดมกลิ่นผิดปกติ) = aplasia of olfactory bulb

Lecture 2

Male reproductive system

Spermatogenesis

   

  • Spermatogenesis = mitosis + meiosis = spermatogonia → spermatozoa
  • Spermatocytogenesis = meiosis = primary spermatocyte → spermatid
  • spermiogenesis = maturation of spermatid
  • Spermiation = release of spermatozoa from sertoli cell

  • Hormone stimulate spermatogenesis
  • Testosterone
  • LH
  • FSH
  • Estrogen
  • GH

Sperm cell

  • Acrosome
  • Hyaluronidase = ย่อย proteoglycan filament (granulosa cell)
  • Proteolytic enzyme = ย่อย protein
  • Flagellum
  • Axoneme = microtubule (9+2)

Sertoli cell

  • Support spermatozoa = nurse cell
  • Form gap junction between sertoli & sperm = regulate spermatogenesis
  • Form tight junction between sertoli & sertoli
  • Blood-testis barrier = กันไม่ให้ WBC มากิน sperm
  • FSH receptor
  • Aromatase enzyme (CYP19) = เปลี่ยน testosterone → estradiol-17β
  • Secrete androgen-binding protein (ABP)
  • Secrete anti-mullerian hormone (AMH)
  • Secrete inhibin B = inhibit FSH

Leydig cell

  • Steroidogenic stromal cell = สร้าง cholesterol → testosterone

Epididymis

  • Head of epididymis = non-motile & incapable of fertilization
  • Tail of epididymis = unidirectionally motile

Vas deferens

Seminal vesicle

  • Secrete mucoid (alkaline) material = 60% of fluid
  • Fructose
  • Citric acid
  • Prostaglandin = กระตุ้นให้ female หลั่ง mucus & uterus contraction
  • Fibrinogen = viscous fibrin coagulum
  • Semenogelin = coagulation of semen

Prostate gland

  • Secrete thin milky fluid (alkaline)
  • Ca, Zn
  • Citrate
  • Phosphate
  • Fibrinogen
  • Pro-fibrinolysin
  • Prostate-specific antigen (PSA) = liquefies coagulated semen
  • Marker of prostate cancer

Sperm activity

↑Sperm activity

  • Alkaline medium
  • ↑temperature = shorten lifespan

↓Sperm activity

  • Acidic medium

Testosterone

Production

  • Location = Leydic cell (steroidogenic cell)
  • Cholesterol → pregnenolone →→→ androstenediol → testosterone
  • 17β-HSD = เปลี่ยน androstenediol → testosterone

Transportation

  • Carrier protein
  • Sex hormone-binding globulin (SHBG) = in circulation
  • Androgen-binding protein (ABP) = in seminiferous tubule
  • Albumin
  • Excretion = kidney
  • Peripheral conversion
  • 5α-reductase = เปลี่ยน testosterone → DHT
  • Type 1 = skin & sebaceous gland
  • Type 2 = urogenital tract & hair follicle
  • aromatase = เปลี่ยน testosterone → estradiol

Action

  • Fetal
  • Development of male sex organ
  • Descent of testes
  • After puberty
  • Direct action (BE & Bass R MALE)
  • Bone
  • Epididymis, vas deferens, seminal vesicle
  • Bass = voice deepening

  • RBC production

  • Muscle mass
  • Abdominal visceral fat
  • Liver = ↑VLDL, ↑LDL, ↓HDL
  • Erectile function
  • DHT action
  • หนวด = Beard growth
  • ตั้ง = Erectile function
  • ไข่ = Scrotum, prostate
  • ย้อย = Sebaceous gland
  • E2 action
  • Skeleton 
  • Testosterone, DHT & E2 action
  • ผลิต = Sperm production
  • ใช้ = Sex drive
  • พอเเล้ว = Negative feedback to gonadotropin secretion

Regulation

  • Sertoli cell
  • Receptor = FSH receptor
  • Secrete = androgen-binding protein & inhibin
  • Inhibin = ↓FSH → ↓testosterone
  • Leydig cell
  • Receptor = LH receptor
  • Secrete = testosterone

Androgen drug

Androgenic : Anabolic effect

  • Testosterone cypionate
  • Methyltestosterone
  • Oxandrolone
  • Stanozolol
  • Danazol
  • Fluoxymesterone

1:1

  • Oxymetholone

1:3

  • Nandrolone

1:4

  • Oxandrolone

1:13

PK

  • Low oral bioavailability = ยกเว้น methyltestosterone

Mechanism

  • Anabolic effect = create structure molecule
  • ↑muscle mass
  • ↑EPO
  • Liver = ↑VLDL, ↑LDL, ↓HDL
  • Androgenic effect = male characteristic development

Indication

  • Male hypogonadism
  • Male delayed puberty
  • Andropause

ADR

  • Aggression, excessive sexual arousal
  • ↑hematocrit, hypertension
  • Early closure of epiphyseal plate
  • Prostate gland enlargement & risk of prostate cancer
  • Priapism
  • Hepatotoxicity

GnRH agonist

  • Gonadorelin 
  • Short-acting GnRH
  • Stimulate in pulsatile fashion
  • ↑LH & FSH secretion
  • Leuprolide
  • Histrelin
  • Nafarelin
  • Goserelin
  • Long-acting GnRH
  • Overstimulation = desensitization
  • ↓LH & FSH secretion

Indication

  • Short-acting
  • Test for cause of hypogonadism
  • ↑LH = tertiary hypogonadism
  • ↓LH = secondary hypogonadism
  • Induce ovulation
  • ↑spermatogenesis
  • Long-acting
  • Prostate cancer
  • Breast cancer
  • Endometriosis
  • Precocious puberty

ADR

  • Thrombosis
  • Menopause symptom

GnRH antagonist

  • Cetrorelix
  • Ganirelix
  • Abarelix

Indication

  • ↑chance of pregnancy
  1. Use mid-cycle to inhibit LH surge
  2. Delay ovulation & ↑thickness of endometrium
  3. ↑chance of implantation
  • Metastatic prostate cancer

ADR

  • Ectopic pregnancy
  • Thrombosis

Androgen receptor antagonist

Indication

  • Nonsteroid
  • Flutamide
  • Bicalutamide
  • Nilutamide
  • Prostate cancer
  • Steroid
  • cyproterone
  • Hirsutism
  • Excessive sexual drive

5alpha-reductase inhibitor

  • Finasteride
  • Dutasteride

Mechanism

  • Inhibit testosterone → DHT conversion

Indication

  • BPH
  • Male pattern baldness

ADR

  • Erectile dysfunction
  • ↓libido

PDE5 inhibitor

  • Sildenafil

Mechanism

  • Inhibit phosphodiesterase type 5 in smooth muscle of penis
  • ↑cGMP
  • Smooth muscle relaxation & vasodilation
  • Penile erection

Indication

  • Erectile dysfunction

ADR

  • Hypotension
  • Flushing, headache
  • Dyspepsia
  • Nasal congestion
  • Cyanopsia = abnormal color vision
  • ห้ามใช้คู่กับ nitroglycerin = severe hypotension
  • Drug interaction = antifungal, antiretroviral (ARV-antiHIV)

Lecture 4

Pathophysiology of male reproductive system

Male hypogonadism

   

  • Diagnosis
  • มี symptom ของ testosterone deficiency
  • Low serum testosterone < 300 ng/dL

Sequence of puberty

  • Male puberty age = 9-14 y
  • Female puberty age = 8-13 y

  1. Testicular enlargement
  2. Penis and pubic hair development

Eunuchoidism 

  • Prepubertal fat distribution
  • High pitched voice
  • Poor muscle mass
  • Arm span - height > 5cm
  • Pubic symphysis to floor - head to pubic symphysis > 5cm
  • Small testis < 4ml
  • No androgen-dependent hair
  • Infantile genitalia
  • ± gynecomastia

Clinical feature of testosterone deficiency

Sexual

Physical

Psycho

Most specific

  • Erectile dysfunction
  • Gynecomastia
  • Hot flushing

Non specific

  • Normochromic anemia
  • ↓Muscle mass
  • Obese
  • Low motivation
  • Sleep disturbance
  • Poor concentration

Free testosterone measurement

  • Gold standard test (free T)
  • Equilibrium dialysis
  • Centrifugal ultrafiltration
  • Calculated free T = จาก total T, SHBG & albumin

  • Immunoassay = inaccurate

  • Normal test (total T) = fasting morning testosterone เเละตรวจ 2 วัน
  • จะใช้การตรวจ free T เเทน total T ก็ต่อเมื่อมีอาการที่ทำให้ free T ≠ calculated free T
  • ↓SHBG = ↓bound T
  • ↑SHBG = ↑bound T
  • Obesity
  • DM
  • Exogenous steroid
  • Nephrotic syndrome
  • Hypothyroidism
  • Acromegaly
  • Aging
  • HIV
  • Cirrhosis
  • Hyperthyroidism
  • Anticonvulsant
  • Exogenous estrogen

Monitoring for testosterone therapy

  • Hct (most important)
  • PSA (prostate-specific Ag) & DRE (digital rectal examination)
  • BMD (bone)

ADR of testosterone treatment

  • Polycythemia
  • BPH & prostate cancer

Erectile dysfunction

  • เป็น risk factor ของ cardiovascular & metabolic disease
  • Main cause = DM

Treatment

  • Lifestyle changing
  • PDE5 inhibitor
  • Low-intensity shockwave therapy = ↑vascular
  • Testosterone
  • ให้เฉพาะในคนที่เป็น hypogonadism & ↓libido

Effect

Not effect

  • Sexual desire
  • Nocturnal penile erection
  • Volume of ejaculate
  • Response to PDE inhibitor
  • Ejaculatory dysfunction
  • Orgasm

  • ADR of exogenous testosterone
  • Inhibit GnRH secretion
  • Inhibit spermatogenesis

Lecture 5

Epididymo-orchitis

  • Infection of epididymis / testis
  • Cause
  • UTI = E. coli
  • STD (sexual transmitted disease)

= chlamydia, gonorrhea

  • Virus = mumps
  • TB
  • Sign & symptom
  • Painful hemiscrotum, erythematous scrotum
  • Thickened of epididymis & vas deferens
  • Fever
  • UTI symptom
  • Penile discharge
  • Diagnosis = ultrasound
  • Hyperperfusion
  • ± hydrocele

Testicular torsion

  • Twisting of spermatic cord → ↓blood flow = ischemic (หลัง 4-8 h)
  • เเบ่งเป็น 2 ชนิด
  • Extravaginal torsion
  • Location = เกิดก่อนเข้า tunica vaginalis
  • Age = perinatal
  • Intravaginal torsion
  • Location = เกิดใน tunica vaginalis
  • Age = adolescence > bell-clapper deformity

  • Sign & symptom
  • Acute severe unilateral pain
  • N/V
  • Ipsilateral higher riding testicle in the hemiscrotum
  • Transverse orientation
  • Anterior epididymis
  • No cremasteric reflex
  • Diagnosis = ultrasound
  • hypoperfusion

Testis neoplasm

Germ cell tumor

Nonseminomatous germ cell tumor

  • Seminoma = most common
  • Embryonal carcinoma = worst prognosis
  • Yolk sac tumor
  • Teratoma
  • Choriocarcinoma

  • Diagnosis
  • Scrotal ultrasound
  • Serum tumor marker
  • AFP (alpha fetoprotein) = yolk sac tumor
  • hCG (human chorionic gonadotropin) = choriocarcinoma
  • LDH (lactate dehydrogenase)

Hydrocele

  • Fluid in tunica vaginalis
  • เเบ่งเป็น 2 ชนิด
  • Communicating hydrocele = fluid from peritoneal cavity
  • Processus vaginalis ไม่ปิด
  • Non-communicating hydrocele = delayed fluid absorption

  • Sign & symptom
  • Communicating hydrocele
  • Painless bulge
  • ขนาดเล็กลงถ้านอนราบ
  • Non-communicating hydrocele
  • Unable to palpate testis
  • Can get above the swelling
  • Positive transillumination test
  • Scrotal ultrasound

Spermatocele

  • Cause = cystic accumulation of semen in epididymal tubule / rete testes / effect ductule
  • Sign & symptom
  • Swelling separate from body of testis
  • Negative transillumination test
  • Smaller than hydrocele
  • Diagnosis = ultrasound
  • Well-defined epididymal hypoechoic lesion

Phimosis

  • Inability to retract prepuce
  • Cause
  • Age = จะดีขึ้นตามอายุ
  • fibrosis
  • Complication
  • Paraphimosis
  • Balanoposthitis = penile infection
  • UTI
  • Cancer

Paraphimosis

  • Prepuce ติดอยู่หลัง glan penis
  • Treatment
  • Manual reduction
  • Dorsal slit = child
  • Circumcision = adult

Paraffinoma

  • Cause = injection of liquid paraffin
  • Complication
  • Painful erection
  • Paraphimosis
  • Infection, necrosis

Penile fracture

  • Cause = rupture of tunica albuginea
  • Ventrolateral part = most common location
  • Sign & symptom = eggplant deformity
  • Swelling
  • Discoloration
  • Deformity toward injury
  • Hemorrhage at scrotum = buck’s fascia rupture

Penis neoplasm

  • Most common cancer type = squamous cell carcinoma
  • Risk factor
  • No neonatal circumcision
  • Phimosis
  • Poor hygiene
  • HPV
  • Smoking
  • Trauma

Penile intraepithelial neoplasia

  • Location
  • Glans of penis = erythroplasia of Queyrat
  • Shaft of penis = Bowen’s disease

Invasive carcinoma of penis

  • Location = glans of penis > prepuce > shaft
  • Lymph node metastasis = femoral & iliac node

จากเอกสารเพิ่มเติม L5

LUTS (lower urinary tract symptom)

  • เเบ่งเป็น 2 ประเภท
  • Storage symptom (irritative LUTS)
  • Frequency > 8/d
  • Urgency
  • Nocturia > 2
  • Dysuria
  • Voiding symptom (obstructive LUTS)
  • Weak urinary stream
  • Hesitancy
  • Incomplete urinary emptying
  • Intermittency
  • Straining
  • Postvoid dribbling
  • Urinary retention
  • Common cause
  • Storage symptom
  • Overactive bladder
  • Cystitis
  • Voiding symptom
  • BPH
  • Prostate cancer
  • Urethral stricture
  • Meatal stenosis = narrowing of the urethral opening
  • Phimosis

BPH (benign prostatic hyperplasia)

  • Most common location = transitional zone
  • Cause = ↑testosterone → DHT → ↑GH → cell proliferation
  • Diagnosis
  • Digital rectal examination (DRE) = rubbery & smooth
  • PSA screening

PSA (prostate specific Ag)

  • Glycoprotein that secreted from prostate epithelial cell
  • Function = ↓viscosity of semen

Malignant neoplasm of prostate gland

  • Most common location = peripheral zone
  • Most common cancer type = adenocarcinoma
  • Diagnosis
  • DRE = hard & rough
  • PSA

Pathology of male reproductive system

Prostate

  • Cell marker
  • Secretory columnar epithelium
  • Low molecular weight Cytokeratins
  • PSA

  • Prostein
  • Basal cuboidal epithelium
  • High molecular weight Cytokeratins
  • P63
  • Neoplastic secretory cell
  • AMACR

Prostatitis

  • Clinical feature
  • Fever
  • ไม่มีใน chronic bacterial prostatitis & chronic pelvic pain syndrome
  • Dysuria
  • Tender prostate on PR exam
  • Low back pain

Bacterial / viral prostatitis

  • Bacteria = E. coli
  • Virus = adenovirus, cytomegalovirus

Chronic nonbacterial prostatitis

(chronic pelvic pain syndrome)

  • Prostatitis ที่ไม่ได้เกิดจาก infection

Granulomatous prostatitis

  • BCG ที่ฉีดเข้าไปเพื่อรักษา urothelial carcinoma
  • TB
  • Fungal = immunocompromised host

IgG4-related prostatitis

  • Plasma cell หลั่ง IgG4 → fibrosis

BPH (benign prostatic hyperplasia)

  • Location = transitional & periurethral zone
  • Clinical feature
  • Urinary bladder distention
  • Urine retention
  • Recurrent bacterial UTI
  • Cause
  • Normal mechanism
  1. Stromal cell ใช้ 5α-reductase type 2 เปลี่ยน testosterone → DHT
  2. DHT กระตุ้น stromal cell & epithelial cell ให้สร้าง GH
  3. DHT กระตุ้น stromal cell ให้สร้าง TGFβ
  4. TGFβ
  • กระตุ้น stromal cell proliferation
  • ยับยั่ง epithelial cell proliferation
  • Abnormal mechanism
  1. ปริมาณ DHT & estrogen เพิ่มขึ้น
  2. เกิด epithelial cell proliferation > cell death

Oogenesis

  • 1st polar body = finish meiosis I
  • Secondary oocyte stop (graafian follicle) = MII
  • 2nd polar body = finish meiosis II

Menstrual cycle

Ovulation

Follicular phase

↑FSH

  • Development of follicle
  • Follicle secrete
  • Inhibin
  • Estrogen

↑inhibin

↑estrogen

↓FSH

  • Only follicle with most FSH receptor survive = dominant follicle
  • Inhibin & estrogen inhibit FSH secretion = ↓FSH

Ovulation

↑LH

↑FSH

  • Ovulation
  • Luteinization = differentiation of granulosa cell

Luteal phase

(fixed 14d)

↑progesterone

↑estrogen

  • Corpus luteum secrete progesterone
  • Maintain endothelium of uterus
  • ↑body temperature
  • Progesterone & estrogen inhibit FSH/LH secretion

Menstruation

↓progesterone

↓estrogen

↓inhibin

  • ไม่มี progesterone = menstruation

   

Ovaries

   

  • Follicular phase
  • Theca cell
  • LH receptor
  • Convert cholesterol → androstenedione
  • Granulosa cell
  • เป็น true avascular epithelium
  • FSH receptor
  • Convert androstenedione → estrone (E1) → estradiol (E2)
  • Zona pellucida = prevent polyspermy
  • Antrum = เเบ่ง granulosa cell เป็น 2 ชั้น
  • Mural layer = เปลี่ยนเป็น corpus luteum
  • Cumulus layer = ติดไปกับ oocyte ตอน ovulation
  • Ovulation
  • Mittelschmerz = abdominal pain from ovulation
  • Luteal phase
  • Granulosa cell
  • Uptake cholesterol ได้เอง
  • เกิด vascularization
  • ↑LDL-R & HDL-R
  • Convert cholesterol → progesterone
  • เเต่ estradiol ยังต้องใช้ androstenedione จาก theca cell เพราะไม่มี CYP17

  • Cholesterol → androstenedione

17β-HSD

  • Estrone → E2

Uterus

  • ↑estrogen

  • ↑estrogen
  • Mucous = ↑thin & elastic (spinnbarkeit)
  • Fern-like pattern
  • Secretory phase
  • ↑progesterone

  • Cervical mucus
  • Bartholin’s gland
  • Transudate from blood vessel

  • Glycogen ถูกย่อยด้วย Lactobacillus → acid = prevent infection

Pregnancy

Sperm capacitation        

  1. Sperm bind to zona pellucida = ↑Ca inside sperm
  2. Exocytosis of acrosome
  3. Sperm fuse w/ oocyte = ↑Ca inside oocyte → cortical granule
  4. Exocytosis of cortical granule → harden of zona pellucida

   

Implantation

  • location = posterior fundus of uterus
  • Syncytiotrophoblast
  • Adhesion & invasion to endometrium
  • Secrete hCG & progesterone
  • hCG = prevent luteolysis
  • ↑hCG = cause morning sickness
  • Decidual cell
  • Secret TIMPs (tissue inhibitor of metalloproteinases)
  • Regulate invasion of syncytiotrophoblast
  • Abnormal = placenta accreta

Maternal-placental-fetal unit

  • Maternal = ได้ progesterone, E2/3 จาก placenta
  • Placenta = ได้ cholesterol & DHEAS จาก maternal
  • Convert cholesterol → pregnenolone → progesterone
  • Convert DHEAS → E2
  • Convert 16α-OH-DHEA → E3
  • Fetus = ได้ pregnenolone จาก placenta
  • Convert pregnenolone → DHEAS
  • Convert DHEAS → 16α-OH-DHEAS

  • Progesterone
  • maintain myometrium
  • Estrogen
  • ↑uteroplacental blood flow
  • ↑breast growth
  • hCS (human chorionic somatomammotropin) / hPL (human placental lactogen) = GH + prolactin
  • ↑glucose = insulin resistance
  • ↓glucose utilization
  • ทำให้เกิด gestational DM

Parturition

   

  1. Fetus ACTH = ↑DHEAS & cortisol
  2. Fetus Cortisol = ↑placenta PGE & CRH
  3. Placenta PGE & E2 = ↑uterus oxytocin receptor

Lactation

  • Mammogenesis = Est & PRL → mammary gland proliferation
  • Lactogenesis = Est, PRL & hPL → milk production
  • Galactogenesis = oxytocin → milk ejection
  • Galactokinesis = maintain milk production

  • Prolactin inhibit GnRH → ↓LH/FSH = no ovulation
  • Lactational amenorrhea

Combined oral contraceptive (COC)

  • ↓translocation of receptor to nucleus
  • ↑degradation of estrogen

Aromatase inhibitor

  • Mechanism
  • Anastrozole, letrozole = selective non-steroidal inhibitor
  • Exemestane = steroidal irreversible inhibitor

Therapy for prostate cancer

  • GnRH agonist = leuprolide, goserelin
  • Anti-androgen = flutamide, bicalutamide

Anti-androgen → flutamide, bicalutamide

  • Bicalutamide + GnRH analog = ↓tumor flare

GnRH agonist → goserelin, leuprolide

  • Mechanism
  • Short-term = stimulate FSH/LH secretion → tumor flare
  • Treat = ให้คู่กับ androgen receptor antagonist → bicalutamide
  • Long-term = desensitize GnRH receptor → inhibit FSH/LH secretion

Therapy for uterine cancer

  • ใช้ hormonal therapy ได้ เเต่ไม่ค่อยได้ผล
  • Progesterone agonist = ↓hyperplasia

Lecture 20

Physiology of pregnancy

Reproductive tract change

Uterus

  • Uterus hypertrophy
  • Dextrorotation (w12) = rotate to the right
  • ↑Uteroplacental blood flow ← ↓Vascular resistance
  • Vasodilator = NO
  • Uterine contraction
  • 2nd trimester = braxton hicks contraction
  • Irregular, unpredictable

Pregnancy position & CO

Supine decubitus position

  • Uterus compress IVC → ↓CO

Lateral decubitus position

  • Uterus not compress IVC → ↑CO

Ovaries

  • Corpus luteum secrete progesterone = 6-7w
  • ถ้าเอา corpus luteum ออกก่อน 7w → spontaneous abortion

Cervix

  • Rearrangement in collagen network
  • Hyperplasia & hypertrophy of cervical gland

  • Secrete mucus = immunoglobulin & cytokine → immunological barrier
  • Eversion = proliferation of columnar cell onto ectocervix
  • Chadwick sign = ↑vascularity → violet color of vagina & cervix

Vagina

  • ↓pH
  • Hypertrophy of smooth muscle

Breast

  • Large & hyperpigmented nipple
  • Colostrum = thick, yellowish fluid (1st milk)

Hematologic change

  • ↑blood volume → ↓blood viscosity & ↓Hct
  • ต้องการ iron ที่มากขึ้น
  • Normal = 300mg
  • Pregnancy = 1000mg

Immunological function

  • Suppression of humoral & cell-mediated immunological function
  • เพื่อไม่ให้ response กับ semiallogeneic fetal graft
  • ↑WBC count
  • ↓Th1
  • ↑Th2 = Th2 bias
  • ทำให้โรคที่ใช้ Th2 อาการเเย่ลง

Coagulation & fibrinolysis

  • ↑all clotting factor ยกเว้น fXI & fXIII
  • ↓protein C & S
  • ↑procoagulant & ↓anticoagulant ทำให้มีโอกาสเกิด thrombosis สูง
  • ↓platelet
  • Hypersplenism
  • ↑blood volume

Cardiovascular system

  • EKG change
  • Left- axis deviation = lead I (+) & lead aVF (-)
  • Elevated diaphragm → heart shift position
  • Q wave in lead II, III, aVF
  • Heart sound = จาก ↑blood volume
  • Systolic murmur
  • S3
  • ↑HR
  • เเต่ยัง <100 bpm
  • ↑CO
  • ↓vascular resistance
  • ↓arterial pressure = ถึง 25w หลังจากนั้นจะเพิ่มขึ้น

Respiratory system

  • Physiologic dyspnea
  1. RR↔︎ เเต่ tidal volume↑
  2. ทำให้ ↓pCO2 = progesterone กระตุ้นให้ ↑sensitivity of CO2
  3. เกิด respiratory alkalosis → ↑HCO3

Double Bohr effect = การเเลกเปลี่ยน gas ระหว่าง fetal & maternal RBC

  1. CO2 transfer to mother
  2. ↑fetal pH
  3. ↑fetal oxygen affinity
  1. CO2 transfer from fetus
  2. ↓maternal pH
  3. ↓maternal oxygen affinity

Metabolic change

Water

  • Water retention

Carbohydrate

  • Fasting hypoglycemia
  • Postprandial hyperglycemia
  • Insulin resistance → hyperinsulinemia

Electrolyte & mineral

  • ↓Na, K & Mg

  • ↑iodine requirement = ต้องใช้ผลิต thyroid hormone ของทั้ง maternal & fetus
  • ↔︎phosphate

Urinary system

  • Dilation of renal pelvis, calyces & ureter
  • Right > left = จาก dextrorotation of uterus
  • Hydronephrosis & hydroureter
  • ↑GFR

urinalysis

  • Glucosuria = จาก ↑GFR
  • Hematuria = จาก contamination
  • Proteinuria 

Gastrointestinal tract

  • Appendix ขยับไปด้านบน
  • ถ้าเป็น appendicitis จะเจ็บที่ right flank pain เเทน
  • ↓lower esophageal sphincter tone
  • GERD
  • ↓gallbladder contractility
  • Cholesterol gallstone
  • Constipation = จาก ↑rectal vein pressure below uterus
  • Hemorrhoid

Endocrine system

Pituitary gland

  • Hypertrophy & hyperplasia of lactotroph = จาก estrogen
  • ↑prolactin
  • ↑gonadotroph
  • ↓somatotroph = จาก negative feedback ของ placental GH
  • Placenta GH เริ่มหลั่งตอน 6w

Thyroid gland

  • Thyroid gland enlargement = เพื่อผลิต thyroid hormone ให้ maternal & fetus
  • Fetal thyroid เริ่ม concentrate iodine = 11w
  • Fetal thyroid เริ่ม secrete thyroid hormone = 20w
  • ↔︎TRH
  • ↓TSH (thyrotropin) ในช่วง 1st trimester = จาก negative feedback ของ hCG
  • ↑TBG
  • ↑total T3/4
  • ↔︎ free T3/4

Parathyroid gland

  • Pregnancy Ca requirement = 400 mg/d
  • Fetus Ca requirement for form skeleton = 3000 mg
  • ↑kidney Ca secrete = จาก ↑GFR
  • Maternal hypercalciuria
  • ↑1,25 vitamin D synthesis
  • ↓plasma albumin
  • ↓total Ca
  • ↔︎ionized Ca
  • ↑bone resorption = osteoporosis

Maternal & fetal Ca transportation

  • Active transport
  • ขึ้นกับ PTH-related protein (PTHrP)
  • เกิดขึ้นตอน 3rd trimester

Adrenal gland

  • ↑ACTH
  • ↑aldosterone

Skin & hair

  • Chloasma (melasma gravidarum) = mask of pregnancy
  • Linea nigra = hyperpigmentation line in anterior abdominal wall
  • Diastasis recti = midline separation of rectus muscle

  • Palmar erythema

Musculoskeletal system

  • Symphyseal separation

Lecture 26

Pharmacology of pregnancy and lactation

Factor affecting placental drug transfer

  • Highly lipid-soluble = ↑easily to fetus
  • ความเร็วในการผ่านขึ้นกับ placental blood flow
  • Highly ionized drug = ↓hardly to fetus
  • Large molecular size = ↓hardly to fetus
  • Heparin ไม่ผ่าน placenta ใช้ใน pregnancy ได้ เพื่อลดภาวะ hypercoagulable state
  • ↑pH (basis) = ↑trap in fetus
  • Maternal blood pH = 7.4
  • Fetal blood pH = 7.3
  • Basis drug จะทำให้เกิด ion trapping ใน fetus
  • ↑protein binding = ↓hardly to fetus
  • จะมีผลชัดเจนก็ต่อเมื่อ poorly lipid-soluble & ionized

Placental transporter

  • มีเเค่ IgG ที่ผ่าน placenta ได้ โดยผ่านได้หลัง 2nd trimester
  • Transporter ที่ efflux ยาออกจาก fetus
  • P-glycoprotein transporter = viral protease inhibitor (anti-HIV)
  • BCRP & MRP3 transporter = hypoglycemic drug

Placental & fetal drug metabolism

  • Placenta สามารถเป็นได้ทั้ง semipermeable barrier & site of metabolism
  • Ethanol → toxic metabolite
  • Pentobarbital → oxidized pentobarbital
  • Prednisolone → inactive prednisone = ใช้ใน pregnancy ได้
  • Fetal alcohol syndrome (FAS)
  • Diagnosis (2/3)
  • Short palpebral fissure
  • Thin vermillion border
  • Smooth philtrum
  • Symptom
  • Growth retardation
  • CNS defect
